#
# A file's journey: what happens when the guest reads or writes a file.
# Render: d2 docs/diagrams/02-file-path.d2 docs/diagrams/02-file-path.svg

title: |md
  # A file's journey — from the guest to durable storage
| {near: top-center; style.font-size: 28}

explanation: |md
  A guest program just reads and writes files like normal.
  Underneath, this binary turns each operation into one broker call.
  **The bytes only ever travel through one unix socket, and the guest never holds a key.**
| {near: top-left; style: {fill: "#fafafa"; stroke: "#bbb"; font-size: 14}}

read: "READING a file" {
  style: {fill: "#eef3ff"; stroke: "#3b5bcf"; stroke-width: 2; border-radius: 16; font-color: "#1f2f7a"}
  direction: down
  r1: "1. Program calls read()" {style.fill: "#d6e0ff"}
  r2: "2. rclone VFS — warm cache?\nyes - answer locally, done" {style.fill: "#d6e0ff"}
  r3: "3. cache miss - ocufs backend\nasks for the bytes by uuid" {style.fill: "#ffffff"}
  r4: "4. brokerrpc sends fileDownload\n(intent=read, downloadable=false)" {style.fill: "#ffffff"}
  r5: "5. broker checks who you are,\nsigns + fetches, streams bytes back" {style: {fill: "#d6ffe0"; stroke: "#2e9e54"}}
  r1 -> r2 -> r3 -> r4 -> r5
}

write: "WRITING a file" {
  style: {fill: "#fff1f0"; stroke: "#cf3b3b"; stroke-width: 2; border-radius: 16; font-color: "#7a1f1f"}
  direction: down
  w1: "1. Program calls write() + close()" {style.fill: "#ffd6d1"}
  w2: "2. rclone VFS stores the bytes\nin the local cache - close returns" {style.fill: "#ffd6d1"}
  w3: "3. in the background, ocufs uploads\nthe file in chunks (fileUpload)" {style.fill: "#ffffff"}
  w4: "4. brokerrpc streams the chunks\n(intent=write, declared size)" {style.fill: "#ffffff"}
  w5: "5. broker checks who you are,\nsigns + writes it to storage" {style: {fill: "#d6ffe0"; stroke: "#2e9e54"}}
  w1 -> w2 -> w3 -> w4 -> w5
}

notes: |md
  **Two things worth knowing**
  - A warm read never leaves the guest — that is why the end-to-end gate proves
    the broker path by reading the broker's own store, not the local cache.
  - If the broker is throttling, the upload backs off and retries — the bytes are
    never lost, just delayed (SEC-46).
| {near: bottom-center; style: {fill: "#fffbe6"; stroke: "#d4a017"; font-size: 13}}
